# normal command
git init: initialize a project as a git project
git add [. or fileName]: add files to stage
git commit [--m 'massages']: commit files to local reposiroty
git log [--pretty=online --abbrev-commit --all --graph]: show commit log
git reflog: show log of actions
git reset --hard commitID: resset version to specified version with

# branch command
git branch: show all branches
git branch branchName: create a new branch
git branch -d branchName: delete a branch with inspection
git branch -D branchName: delete a branch forcibly
git checkout branchName: switch to specified branch
git checkout -b branName: create a new branch and switch to it

# repository
git remote: show remote repository
git remote add origin [remote repository location]: add a remote repository [name origin]
git push origin master:master: push local repository to remote one [name origine], local master branch to remote master branch
git push --set-upstream origin master:master: bind local master branch with remote master branch, then just need to type 'git push' when on the master branch

ssh -T git@github.com: to test if it work with ssh
